Yeah I agree - I just started writing this and I think we should actually put the `TxValidationState` and `m_base_fees` into the `MemPoolAccept::Workspace` (since we need access throughout validation), then return whichever is appropriate at the end.

How does this look?
```c

struct MempoolAcceptSuccess {
    std::list<CTransactionRef> m_replaced_transactions;
    CAmount m_base_fee;
}

using MempoolAcceptResult = std::variant<MempoolAcceptSuccess, TxValidationState>;
using PackageAcceptResult = std::variant<std::vector<MempoolAcceptSuccess>, std::tuple<uint256, TxValidationState>>;
```

