body:
suggestion:

make std::unordered_map<uint256, bool, SaltedTXIDHasher>, fill it with all the txns in the package set to false, and set true when it's been passed.


Then when you're scanning:

```c++
auto it = txids.find(input.prevout.hash);
if (it == txids.end()) continue;
if (it->second == false) /* invalid /*;
/*
valid
*/
```

If you want to get extra fancy to allocate less memory, this is a tmp struct that lives as long as txids so we can just do ptrs

```c++
std::unordered_map<const *CTransaction, bool, SaltedTxidHasher>
```
where you patch:

```c++
 class SaltedTxidHasher
 {
 private:
     /** Salt */
     const uint64_t k0, k1;
 
 public:
     SaltedTxidHasher();
 
     size_t operator()(const uint256& txid) const {
         return SipHashUint256(k0, k1, txid);
     }
     size_t operator()(const CTransaction*& tx) const {
         return SipHashUint256(k0, k1, tx->GetHash());
     }
 };
```

